      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand your concerns, but it's still recommended to see a doctor to get a proper diagnosis and treatment plan. A swollen ankle, even if you can limp on it, can be a sign of deeper injuries or worse outcomes, such as ligament damage. As for your RICE experience with smaller issues, a bad sprain is a different situation and may require more aggressive treatment to prevent long-term damage or complications. delaying a visit to the doctor may increase the risk of chronic pain or further injury.",
